<?
import button from nest.js in nest.js
Nest.requireJS("base")
?>
<h2>Test of basic AJAX function call and return.</h2>

<p>AJAX basic function test: <? nest.js.button( "Button", "Nest.ajax('hello', {'p0':'A parameter'}, onHello)" ) ?>.</p>
<script language="javascript">
   function onHello( obj ) {
         alert('Received ajax hello: ' + obj.text +
            '\nRepeated parameter: ' + obj.p0 );
   }
</script>

<p>In this example, Nest generates an AJAX call to a "hello" AJAX function we have on the site.
The Nest.ajax method instructs javascript to invoke a "onHello" callback with the results
got via the "hello" call.</p>
<p>This is the code:</p>
<pre>
nest.js.button( "Button", "Nest.ajax('hello', {'p0':'A parameter'}, onHello)" )
</pre>